long_desc.thetext:
I compiled (this is the standard mageia cyrus-imapd package) cyrus-imapd
with (http://web.mit.edu/kerberos/www/) release 1.12.4, but actually
the ptloader enter in loops and floods the journal system logs, in particular with errors:

starting: $Id: ptloader.c,v 1.50 2010/01/06 17:01:58 murch Exp $
ptloader[20531]: PTS module afskrb not supported
cyrus-master[10503]: service ptloader pid 20531 in READY state: terminated abnormally

in a loop. The cyrus process never starts and the journalctl consumes 15% of CPUs.
In the config.log the flag HAVE_AFSKRB is not defined. The problem sound to be in the code: ptclient/ptloader.c


    if (!pts) {
        char errbuf[1024];
        snprintf(errbuf, sizeof(errbuf),
                 "PTS module %s not supported", name);
        fatal(errbuf, EC_CONFIG);
    }

which scans for every option listed in IMAPOPT_PTS_MODULE (which are defined in lib/imapoptions) and sound to be "ldap" and "afskrb". When one is not found then the error is printed and program ptloader exists. The problem is that the afskrb is supported only when HAVE_AFSKRB is defined while the imapoptions doesn't rely on this and defines the pts_module options as:

{ "pts_module", "afskrb", STRINGLIST("afskrb", "ldap") }

and not conditionally. Of course since the imapopts.{c,h} are automatically generated trough imapoptions, a conditional #ifdef HAVE_AFSKRB there wouln't work.
